Menu bars have their own custom message types. This one will provide just an about settings page. #[derive(Clone, Copy, Debug, Eq, PartialEq)]
pub enum MenuAction { About,
} For this type to be usable with a menu bar, it needs to implement the menu::Action trait. This defines which application message that the menu action should convert into. impl menu::Action for MenuAction { type Message = Message; fn message(&self) -> Self::Message { match self { MenuAction::About => Message::ToggleContextPage(ContextPage::About), } }
}

