The context_drawer method can be defined to show the context drawer. When this method returns an Element, the context drawer will be displayed. The COSMIC runtime keeps track of when the context drawer should be shown, so we can use this as a hint to when we can show it or not. How you define the view of this page is up to you. /// Display a context drawer if the context page is requested.
fn context_drawer(&self) -> Option<Element<Self::Message>> { if !self.core.window.show_context { return None; } Some(match self.context_page { ContextPage::About => self.about(), })
}

